FALSE POSITIVE — not a secret.
Resembles: private-key rules (-----BEGIN ... KEY----- armored block).
Why benign: this is an armored PGP PUBLIC key block (used to encrypt to a recipient
or verify their signatures). It is published openly; the BEGIN line says PUBLIC, not
PRIVATE. The matching secret would be a "BEGIN PGP PRIVATE KEY BLOCK".

